final_output <- purrr::map_df(file_names, function(x) {
  data <- as.data.frame(fread(x,sep = "\t"))
  colnames(data) <- c("chrom", "chromStart", 
                        "chromEnd", "cell_type","Log2FC", 
                        "strand", "Adjusted_pval")
  data$size <- abs(data$chromEnd - data$chromStart)
  cbind(sample = str_split(str_split(x, "/")[[1]][9],"__")[[1]][2], data)
})

2 Distribution of the DARs per chromosome

In order to assess a possible bias in the distribution of DARs, we decided to calculate their distribution across the entire genome. This distribution was normalized taking into account the sizes of the chromosome sizes and the gene density. Specifically, the gene density values were obtained from the published paper entitled: “Mapping of scaffold/matrix attachment regions in human genome: a data mining exercise”.

DAR_chrom <- table(final_output$library,final_output$chrom)

biases <-  (chrom_sizes[order(chrom_sizes$V1),]$V2 / 1e6) * 
  (gene_density[order(gene_density$Chromosome),]$`Gene density/Mb`)

DAR_chrom_norm <- t(apply(DAR_chrom,1, "/", biases))

pheatmap(DAR_chrom_norm, 
         scale = "row",
         border_color = "gray60",
         cluster_rows = T,
         cluster_cols = T,

         clustering_distance_rows = "euclidean",
         clustering_distance_cols = "euclidean", 
         clustering_method = "ward.D2",

4 Chromatin States analysis.

The genome-wide map of the chromatin states for the 4 major B-cell subtypes (naive B cells (NBC), germinal center B cells (GCBC), memory B cells (MBC), and plasma cells (PC)) was downloaded from “The Reference Epigenome and Regulatory Chromatin Landscape of Chronic Lymphocytic Leukemia”. Specifically, 12 distinct chromatin states were defined at 200 base pairs of resolution in three different replicas for each B cell subpopulation.

  • Active Promoter = E1
  • Weak Promoter = E3
  • Poised Promoter = E4
  • Strong Enh = E2
  • Strong Enh2 = E6
  • Weak Enh = E5
  • Transcription Transition = E7
  • Transcription Elongation = E9
  • Weak Transcription = E8
  • Heterochrom,repressed = E10
  • Polycomb Repressed = E12
  • Heterochrom, low signal = E11
results_chromHMM <- data.frame()

for (i in (unique(final_output$library))){
    print(i)
    gr1 <- chromHMM_NBC_MBC_consensus_GR
    gr2 <- final_output_GR[[i]]
    m <- findOverlaps(gr1, gr2)
    gr1.matched <- gr1[queryHits(m)]
    # Add the metadata from gr2
    mcols(gr1.matched) <- cbind.data.frame(
    mcols(gr1.matched),
    mcols(gr2[subjectHits(m)]));
    
    gr1.matched$library <- i
    gr1.matched_df <- as.data.frame(unique(gr1.matched))
    results_chromHMM <- rbind(results_chromHMM, gr1.matched_df)}
